Program: Discovery
Title: Water Works - Dunwich Port, UK
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryf1
Last Broadcast Date: 03 June 2003
Report from Dunwich port in East Anglia, at one time the largest port in the country. A former medieval city is now a village supporting a few fishing boats following coastal erosion. East Anglia on Britain's south eastern coast is subject to the effects of coastal erosion.